My meme

This is a meme I created about coffee beans. I was inspired by tasting different flavours of coffee from different places after school and studying the effect of different coffee beans on the taste of coffee.

my_meme

library(magick)

# image part one
url_1 <- "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c5/Roasted_coffee_beans.jpg/440px-Roasted_coffee_beans.jpg"
image_1 <- image_read(url_1) %>%
  image_scale(300)

# text of image part one
text_1 <- image_blank(width = 300, height = 225 ,color = "#4d3900") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Coffee Beans", color = "#e1dbd1", size = 20, font = "Impact", gravity = "center")

# image part two
url_2 <- "https://trulyexperiences.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Types-of-Coffee-Beans-All-4-Species-Explained-Pictures.jpg"
image_2 <- image_read(url_2) %>%
  image_scale(300)

#text of image part two
text_2 <- image_blank(width = 300, height = 200, color = "#4d3900") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "For true coffee lovers", color = "#e1dbd1", size = 20, font = "Impact", gravity = "center")

# append the first meme and text together
top_row <- image_append(c(text_1, image_1))
bottom_row <- image_append(c(image_2, text_2))

# the whole meme
meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>% image_append(stack = TRUE) %>% image_scale(600)

# save the meme
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

This is an animated GIF I created about coffee beans, it is an animated GIF that may be of interest to people who like coffee beans, I created it because I myself really enjoy researching different coffee beans.

animation

library(magick)

# first image
url_1 <- "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c5/Roasted_coffee_beans.jpg/440px-Roasted_coffee_beans.jpg"
image_1 <- image_read(url_1) %>%
  image_scale(300)
# second image
url_2 <- "https://trulyexperiences.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Types-of-Coffee-Beans-All-4-Species-Explained-Pictures.jpg"
image_2 <- image_read(url_2) %>%
  image_scale(300)

# creating each frame, add some text by using image_annotate
frame1 <- image_1 %>%
  image_annotate(text = "", size = 300, gravity = "center")
frame2 <- image_1 %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Coffee Beans", size = 40, color = "#e1dbd1", gravity = "center")
frame3 <- image_2 %>%
  image_annotate(text = "", gravity = "center")
frame4 <- image_2 %>%
  image_annotate(text = "For true coffee lovers",size = 32, color = "#e1dbd1",gravity = "center")

#putting the frames in order by using a vector
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)
#Image gradient automation
image_morph(frames)
#creating an animate
animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1)

#save the animated GIF
image_write(animation, "my_animated_GIF.gif")
